Label the hex‐spiral using axial coordinates (q,r) with 1 at (0,0) and the six step‐vectors  
D₀=(1,0), D₁=(0,1), D₂=(−1,1), D₃=(−1,0), D₄=(0,−1), D₅=(1,−1).  
One shows by the usual “go east, then turn clockwise around k ⋅6 cells” construction that the number 2026 lies in ring 26 at  
P=(3, −26).  Its six neighbors are at  
P+D₀=(4,−26), P+D₁=(3,−25), P+D₂=(2,−25),  
P+D₃=(2,−26), P+D₄=(3,−27), P+D₅=(4,−27).  
Working out the spiral‐indices of those six points one finds the six neighbor‐values are  
2025, 1873, 1874, 2027, 2185 and 2184.  Their sum is  
2025+1873+1874+2027+2185+2184 = 12168.
